disruptive i keep wondering why this place hasnt received any bib gourmandbrazils best mentions since its way ahead the vast majority of the listed ones the flavors and techniques at animus ressemble those at the old clos tapas restaurant sadly out of business not the new one with the same name i was missing that meltinyourmouth octopus and finally found another place able to match its flavor and texture every course i had was mix of usual ingredients cooked to perfection elevated with unusual combinations from simple ones like roasted tomato and basil to more complex ones like grounded black olives cheese and nut pralines everything was so well thought and executed that i was left craving more dish after dish high fair price an 8 course meal technically its an 8 dish meal since some of them arrive in pairs and some are sharing which makes the service simplerfaster low the waiters are ok but they lack some training and passion to describe the dishes i usually dont care about this because most of the times i feel like its going to be an overpromiseunderdeliver kind of thing but at animus it was the other way around amazing stuff been narrated like day to day rice and beans
